# Normalize line endings for text source by default (consistent LF in the repo).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Byte-exact Altium .RUL exports are the differential-honesty fixtures: the test
# suite asserts parse->render reproduces them BYTE-FOR-BYTE (incl. the 0xB6 '¶'
# record terminator). Git EOL conversion on Windows (core.autocrlf) would inject
# a stray CR before every LF and break the byte-exact gate. Treat them as binary
# so no platform ever rewrites their bytes.
tests/fixtures/rul/*.RUL -text
*.RUL -text
